  ('Open Philanthropy','New York University',30000,'2015-08-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/labor mobility/RCT','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/new-york-university-support-labor-mobility-rct','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grantee represented by Suresh Naidu and Yaw Nyarko; grant references cause page https://www.openphilanthropy.org/research/cause-reports/labor-mobility',NULL,NULL,'2015-09-23', 'day', 'https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/_m_jhh_KTko',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Protect the People',550000,'2016-02-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/Haiti/US agricultural migration','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/protect-people-seasonal-migration-haiti','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','A second grant in the area; after a 2014 grant described at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/usaim-seasonal-migration-haiti to other organizations. New grant builds on positive and negative lessons from earlier grant. Followup conversation with Sarah Williamson of grantee organization at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/Sarah_Williamson_09-09-16_%28public%29.pdf on 2016-09-09',NULL,NULL,'2016-02-29', 'day', 'https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/MbeaAn2aLXE',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','U.S. Association for International Migration',1310483,'2014-07-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/Haiti/US agricultural migration','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/usaim-seasonal-migration-haiti','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant first published in August 2014; updated with progress report. Grantee was USAIM but project was carried out by it along with International Organization for Migration (IOM). Grant was not repeated next year, but a new grant was made to Protect the People for a similar purpose. On November 1, 2018, the grant amount on the website was reduced from the original of $1,490,505 to an updated value $1,310,483, but no explanation was added',NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','ImmigrationWorks Foundation',285000,'2014-07-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/low-skilled migration promotion','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/immigrationworks-foundation-general-support','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','First major grant to an advocacy group related to promoting more low-skilled migration from the perspective of interests of potential employers of low-skilled workers',NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Center for Global Development',1184720,'2014-03-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/international labor mobility','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/center-global-development-labor-mobility-research','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant supports the CGD research agenda on labor mobility, including 75% of the time of Michael Clemens. Followup conversation with Michael Clemens and Cynthis Rathinasamy of grantee organization at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/Michael_Clemens_and_Cynthia_Rathinasamy_12-15-2015_%28public%29.pdf on 2015-12-15 and again at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/Michael_Clemens_Cynthia_Rathinasamy_06-21-16_%28public%29.pdf on 2016-06-21','Michael Clemens', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','ImmigrationWorks Foundation',150000,'2015-12-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/low-skilled migration promotion','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/immigrationworks-general-support-2016','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Second grant; previous grant made in July 2014. New grant provided based on satisfaction with first grant and review of grantee situation. Followup conversation with Tamar Jacoby of grantee organization at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/Tamar_Jacoby_03-31-16_%28public%29.pdf on 2016-03-31',NULL, NULL, '2015-12-14', 'day', 'https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/G1_h0arIB1Y',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Niskanen Center',360000,'2015-10-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/politics','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/niskanen-immigration','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grantee is a libertarian think tank looking to hire legal counsel. Followup conversation with grantee organization at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/David_Bier_12-14-2015_%28public%29.pdf on 2015-12-14 and again at https://www.openphilanthropy.org/sites/default/files/Niskanen_Center_07-22-16_%28public%29.pdf on 2016-07-22',NULL, NULL, '2015-10-29', 'day', 'https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/tGWpy5thvRY',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Center for Global Development',1800000,'2017-03-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/international labor mobility','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/center-global-development-migration-program','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant supports work at CGD of Michael Clemens and his team. Continues a 2014 grant https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/center-global-development-labor-mobility-research for the same purpose','Michael Clemens','Alexander Berger','2017-06-27','day','https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/DBMCmQJz1Pc',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Protect the People',50000,'2016-10-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/Haiti/US agricultural migration','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/protect-people-exit-grant','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Exit grant to close out support for helping workers from Haiti access season work in the US. See https://www.openphilanthropy.org/may-2017-update-protect-people-grant for a grant update',NULL,'Alexander Berger','2017-10-20','day','https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/jW3KjxVUOOA',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Niskanen Center',400000,'2018-01-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/politics','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/niskanen-immigration-2018','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant over two years to continue to support work on immigration policy. Grant is a renewal of https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/niskanen-immigration and is in recognition of the Niskanen Center growing its immigration program to $1 million/year, while also keeping in mind the expectation of no significant positive movement on immigration at the federal level',NULL,'Alexander Berger','2018-01-30','day','https://groups.google.com/a/openphilanthropy.org/forum/#!topic/newly.published/5XHsBDrlA3Q',NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','MoveOn.org Civic Action',375000,'2015-10-01','month','donation log','Migration policy','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/moveon-civic-action-syrian-refugee-advocacy','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant to support work on Syrian refugee resettlement in the United States. Grant recommended for Cari Tuna to make personally; grantee is a 501(c)(4) organization',NULL,'Alexander Berger','2018-06-09','day',NULL,NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','International Refugee Assistance Project',1000000,'2019-01-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/refugee migration','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/international-refugee-assistance-project-general-support-2018','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant renews May 2016 grant https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/international-refugee-assistance-project-general-support Grantee plans to expand its work to Europe, focusing on family reunification, asylum, and humanitarian visas. In the grant writeup, the donor notes: "our immigration policy work has not focused much on refugee resettlement, which we had assumed would be more crowded than other aspects of immigration policy with funders aimed at supporting increased opportunities for people to move to the U.S. for humanitarian reasons. While we continue to believe that is directionally correct, our increased interest in supporting advocacy around refugee resettlement is partially based on learning more about the fairly limited foundation funding for advocacy around refugee resettlement."',NULL,'Alexander Berger','2019-03-30','day',NULL,NULL),
  ('Open Philanthropy','Center for Global Development',709888,'2019-03-01','month','donation log','Migration policy/international labor mobility','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy/center-global-development-labor-mobility-partnerships','https://www.openphilanthropy.org/focus/us-policy/immigration-policy','Grant over 1.5 years to the Center for Global Development to support a working group on and incubation of a new organization aimed at enhancing international labor mobility. The new organization, called LaMP (Labor Mobility Partnerships), hopes to assist countries negotiating new legal channels for migration on terms of mutual benefit and to generate research and evidence on effective labor mobility regimes, in the ultimate service of reducing global poverty and inequality. Rebekah Smith and Lant Pritchett, who will be working together on the incubation and launch, proposed the idea for this type of organization in a 2016 CGD working paper https://www.cgdev.org/sites/default/files/goldilocks-solution-just-right-promotion-labor-mobility.pdf',NULL,'Alexander Berger','2019-04-19','day',NULL,NULL);
